mkdir - create directories.
ls - List directory contents.
cd - change directories.
pwd - current path.
su - super user
vi or vim - text editor.
cp - copy files or directories.
mv - move files or directories.
rm - remove files.
rmdir - remove directories.
cat - concatnate file.
echo - display string given.
grep - find the pattern in the files.
chmod - change file permissions.
chown - change owner of the files & folder. 
passwd - update the user or root password
who - it will show logged on user.
tar - archive a files.
zip - compress the files or directories.
ssh- secure connection for remote login.
reboot -reboot the system.
poweroff - shutdown the system.
hostname - print the system name.
ifconfig - print the network details like IP address , Mac address, NIC ID.
adduser - user creation
addgroup - group creation.
usermod - to add the user into group.
